FT  21 APR 94 / World Trade News: Pepsi grouping buys bottler
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SHAHIRA IDRISS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CAIRO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Pepsi Cola International is part of a consortium which has bought its
Egyptian franchisee, Egyptian Bottling Company (EBC), Shahira Idriss reports
from Cairo. The EPounds 157.6m (Pounds 32m) sale is the country's first
industrial privatisation. Apart from Pepsi Cola, the Alcan Bugshan
Investments consortium comprises Bugshan &amp; Brothers, which cans Pepsi in
Saudi Arabia, and the Egyptian Alcan Group. EBC's eight plants produced 22m
cases of Pepsi last year, supplying 45 per cent of Pepsi's volume in Egypt.
They have a capacity to supply more than two-thirds.
