controlling interest in Hong Kong's South China Morning Post newspaper
group.
Mr Liem, an Indonesian Chinese, is generally regarded as Indonesia's richest
businessman with interests ranging from cement manufacturing to noodle
making. The Salim group, Mr Liem's main company, had turnover of more than
Dollars 9bn last year.
The fortunes of both Mr Kuok and Mr Liem were founded on the commodities
business.
